; Manuscript
INUMBER 202
NAME 236
MISC
VOLUME 1
WEIGHT 1
IFPREVERB GET -1
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! 99
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You can't take that.
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB STEAL -1
        IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! 99
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER What would you steal? Words?
        ENDIF
ENDIF
HIDDEN
IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 99
        IFPREVERB READ -1
                CLEARVERB
                IFVAR UNDEAD = 1
                        ECHO PLAYER Your eyes try to trace the indecipherable script, but it is not a recognizable alphabet.
                ENDIF
                IFVAR UNDEAD = 0
                        ECHO PLAYER The manuscript reads, "Greetings, whoever you may be. I am Keromist, Sage of Salicae. This volume is warded- no ghoul nor any other undead or demon can read it. If you are reading this, know the following..."
                        ECHO PLAYER "One of my apprentices has taken over my tower and I am most probably dead. But I have looked into the mists in the Tower of Blood and seen one probable fate... if you have seen me, and yet you hold this book..."
                        ECHO PLAYER "...that I am mindless, my brain burned away by energies of hostile forces. I can be cured through the administration of a horbult leaf."
                        ECHO PLAYER "Please, aid me, I beg of you, if this is the case. I will be most grateful should you aid in my recovery."
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
ENDIF
